brainly_data.question: What do homologous structures have in common
brainly_data.subject: Biology

all_answers.question: What do homologous structures have in common
all_answers.subject: Biology
all_answers.text: A homologous structure is an example of an organ or bone that appears in different animals, underlining anatomical commonalities demonstrating descent from a common ancestor. In other words, it's when very different animals have bones that appear very similar in form or function and seem to be related.
